## How to nominate a school when nominations are open
It only takes a few minutes to nominate. If your school is successful they can
join the 200 schools that have been awarded this honour when the awards were
first run, and the 151 schools who have received the award since October 2018.
We're delighted to add the list of successful schools for 2019/20 towards the
Remember by taking part, your school be recognised as setting a great standard
* A beautiful trophy, which is valid for two years.
* Use of the Good Diabetes Care in School Award logo on all your print and digital stationery.
* Feature on the Diabetes UK Honour Wall.
* An opportunity for positive local media attention about your school’s achievements.
* Ongoing support from us to help with best practice and updated methods of care.
## What happens after I've made a nomination?
Once the nomination phase closes, we will contact the school informing them of
their nomination. We'll then invite them to apply for the award.
We won't be collecting personal data, names or details of any children who
However, we will ask you to provide data about the school. We'll only use this
